		sed -e "/^#/d" -e s/#.*$$// $(DIR)/networks | awk \
		    '{print $$1, $$0; for (i = 3;i <= NF;i++) print $$i,$$0}' \
		    | makedbm - /etc/yp/$(DOM)/networks.byname; \
		awk 'BEGIN { OFS="\t"; } $$1 !~ /^#/ { print $$2, $$0 }' \
